text.section:
The Department may revoke any license issued under this title if the Department finds that:
False or inaccurate information was willfully, deliberately, or knowingly contained in the application;
Conditions or requirements of the license have been violated;
Substantial deviation from plans, specifications, or requirements has occurred;
The Department has been refused lawful entry to the premises for the purpose of inspecting to insure compliance with the conditions of the license; or
A change in conditions exists that requires temporary or permanent reduction or elimination of the source or discharge of radiation.
